---
const pageTitle = "Fire";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html,
      body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a {
        text-decoration: underline;
      }

      a.blue {
        color: var(--blue);
      }

      a.red {
        color: var(--red);
      }

      a.green {
        color: var(--green);
      }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .topbar span {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 0 8px;
        white-space: nowrap;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
        background:
          linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.94), rgba(245,245,245,0.94)),
          repeating-linear-gradient(
            to bottom,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 0px,
            rgba(0,0,0,0.018) 1px,
            transparent 1px,
            transparent 4px
          );
      }

      .symbol-bg {
        position: absolute;
        top: 50%;
        left: 50%;
        transform: translate(-50%, -50%) rotate(-8deg);
        width: 300px;
        height: 300px;
        opacity: 0.2;
        pointer-events: none;
        user-select: none;
        z-index: 0;
      }

      .symbol-bg svg {
        width: 100%;
        height: 100%;
        display: block;
      }

      .content-layer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 42px;
        line-height: 1.05;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
        font-weight: bold;
        letter-spacing: 0.5px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 15px;
        margin: 0 0 24px;
        text-transform: lowercase;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
        letter-spacing: 1px;
      }

      p {
        margin: 0 0 16px;
      }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px 16px;
        background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #f3f3f3, #ebebeb);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
        box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
        font-weight: bold;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
        font-size: 16px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        display: inline-block;
        margin: 4px 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }

      .content-layer p,
      .content-layer h1,
      .content-layer h2,
      .content-layer .subtitle,
      .content-layer .divider,
      .content-layer .quote,
      .content-layer .mini-links,
      .content-layer .footer-note {
        text-shadow: 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        html,
        body {
          font-size: 17px;
        }

        h1 {
          font-size: 34px;
        }

        .frame {
          padding: 18px 16px 24px;
        }

        .symbol-bg {
          width: 210px;
          height: 210px;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">symbols index</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="green" href="/symbols/mirror">previous</a> ]</span>
        <span>[ <a class="red" href="/symbols/fool">next</a> ]</span>
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <div class="symbol-bg" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none">
            <g stroke="#000000" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M150 46 C178 86, 206 114, 206 148 C206 184, 180 210, 150 210 C120 210, 94 184, 94 148 C94 114, 122 86, 150 46Z" />
              <path d="M150 210 L150 252" />
              <path d="M126 252 L174 252" />
              <path d="M122 146 C132 136, 144 132, 150 118 C156 132, 168 136, 178 146" />
              <path d="M132 170 C140 178, 160 178, 168 170" />
              <path d="M150 78 C162 100, 176 114, 176 136" />
              <path d="M150 78 C138 100, 124 114, 124 136" />
            </g>
          </svg>
        </div>

        <div class="content-layer">
          <h1>Fire</h1>
          <p class="subtitle">symbols / transformation / illumination / archive entry 001</p>

          <div class="divider">***</div>

          <p>
            Fire is one of the oldest and most charged symbols in human life. It warms,
            destroys, protects, reveals, and transforms. Because of this, it often appears
            wherever a change is taking place that cannot simply be reversed. In symbolic
            language it often stands beside the <a class="red" href="/symbols/serpent">serpent</a>,
            the <a class="blue" href="/symbols/labyrinth">labyrinth</a>, or the
            <a class="green" href="/symbols/mandala">mandala</a> as an image of process,
            danger, and transformation.
          </p>

          <p>
            To encounter fire symbolically is to come near intensity. Something is being
            consumed. Something else is being made visible. Fire strips away what cannot
            endure its heat and leaves behind what is more essential.
          </p>

          <div class="quote">
            fire does not argue. it changes what it touches.
          </div>

          <h2 class="section-title">destruction and illumination</h2>

          <p>
            Fire destroys, but it also illuminates. This double nature is part of its
            meaning. In psychological life, moments of crisis, passion, rage, insight,
            or creative breakthrough often carry a fiery quality. They can feel dangerous,
            but they also reveal what was hidden.
          </p>

          <p>
            In this way, fire is not only a symbol of danger. It is a symbol of exposure.
            What has been concealed is suddenly lit. What has been frozen begins to move.
          </p>

          <h2 class="section-title">purification and change</h2>

          <p>
            Fire is also linked to purification. Not because it makes everything gentle,
            but because it burns away excess. The false, the stale, the dead, and the
            unnecessary cannot pass through unchanged.
          </p>

          <p>
            This is why fire often appears in stories of initiation, sacrifice, trial,
            and rebirth. The person who passes through fire does not come back exactly
            the same. In that sense, fire belongs with the <a class="red" href="/symbols/fool">fool</a>
            who risks the unknown, the <a class="blue" href="/symbols/mirror">mirror</a>
            that reveals what is true, and the <a class="green" href="/symbols/tree-of-life">tree of life</a>
            that shows how transformation changes the whole structure of a life.
          </p>

          <div class="mini-links">
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/">back to symbols index</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/fool">continue to: fool</a>
            <a class="red" href="/symbols/mirror">mirror</a>
            <a class="green" href="/symbols/serpent">serpent</a>
            <a class="blue" href="/symbols/tree-of-life">tree of life</a>
            <a class="red" href="/symbols/mandala">mandala</a>
            <a class="green" href="/symbols/labyrinth">labyrinth</a>
          </div>

          <p class="footer-note">
            this page is part of the hidden archive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>